		</key>
		<key>
			<name>Shift-tab</name>
			<desc>Set autobrakes to 0</desc>
		</key>
		<line>Speedbrakes:</line>
		<line>The speedbrakes have 4 settings. At 0, they never extend.</line>
		<line>At 1, they will only fully extend on the ground.</line>
		<line>With the setting at 2, they will extend to about a third</line>
		<line>out, and will go to full if the left gear compresses.</line>
		<line>At 3, they are out fully. (Use with caution!)</line>
		<hrule />
		<line>Engine Startup:</line>
		<line>1. Switch on the battery on electrical panel.</line>
		<line>2. Start APU on electrical panel and wait for its work mode (on EICAS will be message "APU running").</line>
		<line>3. Click on the APU gen.</line>
		<line>4. On engine panel switch on starters (click on knobs) and switch on Autostart button.</line>
		<line>5. Wait for engines idle (on EICAS lights off messages L ENG FAILURE, R ENG FAILURE).</line>
		<line>6. Confirm engine generators are on, then on electrical panel switch off APU GEN and turn off APU.</line>
	</help>

